      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Do not take extra salt or drink a massive amount of water, as this can rapidly push your lithium levels into a dangerous toxic range before you know it. Dehydration can indeed cause these symptoms, but self-treating with salt and water is a dangerous gamble that could lead to seizures or kidney failure. The only safe way to know if it is just dehydration or toxicity is to get your blood checked, so please consider a telehealth visit or a pharmacy consultation to avoid the clinic trip while staying safe.",
